default5.7
default              
defaultAs stated, people with DMD are now living much longer, but the health service has not kept up. This has led to a dearth of services for the adult population and many ‘dropping off’ during transition. 
default5.8 
default              
defaultP
defaults
defaulty
defaultcho-social care is absolutely vital, with families affected by DMD or BMD being at a higher risk of breakup and depression. People living with these conditions must have the option of specialist psycho-social care (not just advice from Care Advisors as set out in the Service Specification). Such care is often not available locally.
